3.2 Accuracy

  • Low accuracy (< 25% correct on one-choice trials, averaged across blocks): Excluding participants due to poor accuracy could be done in multiple ways. Here, we opted to define a criterion for exclusion based on the idea that random presses of buttons should result in 25% correct responses on single-choice trials.

3.3 Misses

  • Excessive missing (< 60 misses across the whole session): 60 is an arbitrarily chosen value. We consider 60 missed trials to reflect major data loss, leading to unreliable estimates of response times, which justifies exclusion.
